MPath

    store paths as parts
    no backslashes

    path methods:

        mpath["path"].exists()
                    .isFile()
                    .isDir()
                    .inP4()
                    .opened() -> [], [sdas, nnacu]
                    .openedBy("sdas") -> False
                    .lastEdited()

        should also work on dot enabled syntax

            mpath.path.exists()
            etc

helps for everything

